This paper is about semantic segmentation using deep learning techniques, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper specifically focuses on the use of Conditional Random Fields (CRFs) in deep neural networks, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of object detection and superpixel based potentials, which are topics related to natural language processing (cs.CL) and multimedia (cs.MM), respectively. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, and cs.MM.
